@@eThe Forest of Confusion@@N

North of @@yKiess@@N, where patrol roads fail under older forces, lies
a forest where travelers do not simply get lost -- they are @@rmisled
by intent@@N. Landmarks repeat out of sequence, bells sound from
impossible directions, and fresh tracks reappear ahead of those
who made them.

Three overlapping systems collide here. @@yKiess civic order@@N pushes
south from the wall with patrol roads, waystones, and bell-posts --
all slowly losing ground as mist incursion contracts the reliable
perimeter each season. The @@gVerdant ecological intelligence@@N -- the
ancient root network's outermost defense -- produces chemical
disorientation and selective path-rerouting to discourage penetration
toward the deep interior. And @@dWithered Conclave residue@@N -- crystal-
hum interference, fungal geometry, and deteriorating quarantine wards
-- weaponizes disorientation into attritional hazard.

The @@rconfusion mists@@N were not natural. They were a deliberately
engineered quarantine created by druids to contain crystal matrices
the @@WSpirebound Conclave@@N embedded in the forest's root systems and
then abandoned. For centuries the druids maintained the containment.
Then the druidic order died -- not dramatically, but demographically.
Without maintenance, the mists lost their calibrated purpose and
diffused outward, making the entire forest directionless.

Ancient residents endure within. @@gTreants@@N guard as territorial
sentinels, some bearing both healthy bark and blight scarring.
@@eCentaurs@@N in secluded glade settlements maintain armed neutrality
toward Kiess, their oral tradition preserving accounts of the forest
before the mists existed. @@rNeogi@@N slavers exploit the fog as cover
for their underground warrens. @@dBroken ones@@N -- humanoids degraded
by prolonged crystal exposure -- congregate in transitional bands
where the quarantine once held.

Deep in the wood, @@rYmmas@@N occupies a fortified cabin that has never
been reclaimed by root growth -- implying either extraordinary power
or a bargain with the forest's intelligence. A Guardian Yugoloth
defends the approach.

The @@rSpider of the Deep Wood@@N hunts the Verdant-Withered boundary,
a solitary apex predator adapted to prey toughened by preservation
magic and crystal resonance.

The Forest of Confusion is the narrative bridge between civilized
western routes and the deeper myth-space of the @@gVerdant Depths@@N
and the @@dWithered Depths@@N below. Three institutions failed in
sequence -- the Conclave created the problem, the druids contained
it, and Kiess manages the symptoms. The forest is the result.
